The cpugrabber program gets cpu idle time 
------------------------------------------

1. run "cpugrabber -r 5000"

This program will print number of iterations run by cpugrabber every 5000 ms.
Use cpugrabber --help for more usage.

2. To capture and process output, run
"cpugrabber -r 5000 -t 20000 2> grabber.out"

Run cpugrabber for a total of 20000 ms (20 seconds) and pipe stderr to
grabber.out file.

Then run
"process-grabber dummy grabber.out" (ignore dummy parameter)

process-grabber will generate the idles iterations in a column



